reviews.review_text: The Seaborn is great. Amazing selection and prices. The people working here are super helpful. I appreciate they always try and help you make the right choice and amount to bring home. The store is kept clean. They have a huge selection of frozen fish as well as fresh fish on ice. Going back for Hamachi (Yellowtail) soon!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Alex for your kind word. That made our day!! We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Good variety of fish available.  Price reasonable. Will come again.

Fresh local seafood market that my family has been going to for years now. The Saturday sashimi special is fresh and delicious! Make sure you call on Friday to put in your preorder!  Hidden gem in marpole :)
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Rachael! The fresh fish season has just started, so we all look forward to serving you soon!

reviews.review_text: It s spot prawn season, purchase great fresh spot prawn for great price! Super delicious
Fresh wild caught fishes available most days. Reasonable prices and fanatics service. Also available in store are Japanese seafood related products.
Very fresh sashimi with reasonable price! The staff is very nice.

Discover this germ by word--of-mouth.  The people there are very helpful and  accomodating  to my request on the order.  Great price , great quality with their fish. Will be my go for fish store from now on.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Loretta! Hope you enjoyed the fish. Looking forward to serving you again! PS: Hope its a gem not germ.

reviews.review_text: Offers many kinds of frozen fishes, fish parts, smoked fishes and sashimi-grade fillets.  For black cod (sablefish), those sold at major supermarkets are all farmed. Here at Seaborn they sell the farmed ones cheaper, and they also carry the more pricey, wild-caught variety. Staff is friendly, and they accept credit cards.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you cm chiu for giving us your valuable comment! Black Cod a.k.a. Sablefish we sell are all wild, so enjoy more Black Cod from us. Thank you and see you soon at the store!

reviews.review_text: Lots of frozen fresh fish. Reasonable price and nice staff.
A great seafood store. If you likes Japanese sashimi grade fish, this is the place to go!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Charity for your generous feedback! Hope we can serve you soon again! If youre interested, we will take orders soon for our annual freshly smoked salmon which is offered only once a year around the end of the year, so hope you can try if you havent yet. THANK YOU!

reviews.review_text: Is a good place to buy frozen fish in very good price, and do have some fresh cut fillets, the best is dollar a bag fish parts that you can make shop base.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your comment Tasman! We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Nice small seafood store. Friendly service and good price.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! We look forward to serving you soon again!

reviews.review_text: Fish are always so fresh and the staff are courteous and patient.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Bonnie! We look forward to serving you again!

reviews.review_text: Have most japanese foodstrhat you need.
So many Sashimi material
sashimi-grade seafood

Good place for quality seafood and sashimi.   However the best deal is the fresh black cod bone (see pic) it is only $1.50 per bag!!! Just slow fry them with a dash of Himalayan salt.  Your taste buds will be so delighted.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow, Ive never fried black cod bones before. Thank you for sharing your wonderful tip to enjoy more black cod!

reviews.review_text: Great place for BC Wild fresh fish at very competitive prices . Highly appreciated Mayus services to help checking and corrected the price. For sure will come more often.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your business with us Patrick! Were always delighted to serve you more. We will have Japanese Mikan Orange around the end of this year, so please order if youre interested. Hope you enjoyed your Idiot Fish (Kinki)!

reviews.review_text: I always visit Seaborn before going to Japan as they have most of what I need for gifts. Matsutake in September/October and komochi kombu are definite favourites. Also popular with my Japanese visitors. Friendly and helpful staff.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your comment! We now offer delivery to your door in Vancouver and Richmond, so we look forward to serving you again!

reviews.review_text: Fresh fish at great price. They will notify you of fresh arrivals on social media!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Sakura for liking our store. Yes, we use Email newsletter, LINE, Instagram and WeChat to notify our customers what are available right now. Thank you and please come back again!

reviews.review_text: good specials on seafood.  selection of cut at home sashimi
Super friendly grat prices and free parking.
Good deal on many fresh fish
Great black cod!
Good place to get pine mushrooms
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you! We have dried one all year around and fresh one in fall. All BC grown. Hope to see you again!

reviews.review_text: Frozen seafood specialty store, supplying all kinds of frozen seafood produced in Canada

Very disappointed in their customer service. I called for an order my mother made but the person who answered was not only unhelpful but also condescending. It made me feel like I don t want to use their service if you don t even value our business. Their products are good. So it s very unfortunate how one staff can make such a bad impression to customers who call to inquire.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Were very sorry to hear your experience with us. This shouldnt happen again to any customers but we think it may have happened especially when we have lots of fresh fish and everyone was super busy. We will try our best from now on and appreciate your time to leave a valuable comment for us.

reviews.review_text: i just bought spot prawn from Seaborn today! and it is already dead for a long while.  Definitely, it is not dead in the way home.
None of the frozen fish here is labeled with origin, dates, farmed or fresh, or anything else to certify quality.  Truly what youre buying here is Asian Mystery Fish.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for taking your time to give us your feedback. We apologize that we confused you with local fish as Asian mystery fish which were not familiar with you. But majority of our fish are caught in local Norther BC while Seabass and Sockeye Salmon are now imported and King Salmon is raised in BC. Of course situation will change but were happy to answer your question anytime for your comport. Hope we can serve you again.

reviews.review_text: Horrible stuff I dont know what B C is talking about, much better elsewhere.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Were sorry to hear your experience with us. If you could let us know your details, we believe we can serve you better. If you have more we can listen, please send an email to info@seaborn.ca Thank you for taking your time in advance.
